Newly recorded from Prince Edward Island. In Nova Scotia generally found in open habitats. In Québec collected in raspberry plantations and pine woods (
Levesque & Levesque 1993
). This is the so-called “corn wireworm” of southern regions. The larva is a soil predator in meadow, field, and ecotonal areas, and facultatively feeds on sprouting corn and other seeds in agricultural situations (P. Johnson, unpublished data).
